# Code in English

All code-related elements must be written in English to maintain consistency and facilitate international collaboration.

## What must be in English:

### ✅ Required
- Variable names
- Function names
- Class names
- Interface names
- Type definitions
- Method names
- Property names
- Constant names
- Enum values
- Code comments (inline and block comments)
- Documentation comments (JSDoc, TSDoc, etc.)
- Git commit messages
- Branch names
- File names (when appropriate)

### ❌ Not required
- User-facing text and strings (can be in Spanish or other languages)
- Content data
- Chat conversations
- Documentation for end users

## Examples:

**Good ✅**
```typescript
// Fetches user data from the API
const fetchUserData = async (userId: string) => {
  // Implementation here
}
```

**Bad ❌**
```typescript
// Obtiene datos del usuario
const obtenerDatosUsuario = async (idUsuario: string) => {
  // Implementación aquí
}
```
